1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:04,470
[Episode 40]

2
00:00:08,870 --> 00:00:10,000
Yes.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:14,270
As you'd requested, I've found out about Ms. Park Dan Dan's biological mother.

4
00:00:14,270 --> 00:00:15,520
Have you?

5
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:20,800
Her mother's name is Kim Ji Young.

6
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:24,590
Kim... Ji Young?

7
00:00:24,590 --> 00:00:28,120
We looked into the hospital records where Ms. Park was born.

8
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:33,090
Her mother's name is recorded as Kim Ji Young.

9
00:00:33,090 --> 00:00:35,830
So we traced Kim Ji Young.

10
00:00:35,830 --> 00:00:41,420
But we only found that she left for the US less than three months after giving birth.

11
00:00:41,420 --> 00:00:48,800
Her whereabouts after that are a bit hazy but would you like us to keep looking?

12
00:00:48,800 --> 00:01:02,270
I heard that my mom abandoned me and ran away when I was an infant less than 100 days old.

13
00:01:02,270 --> 00:01:03,530
Ms. Park.

14
00:01:03,530 --> 00:01:08,420
I don't want to look for the mother who abandoned me.

15
00:01:08,420 --> 00:01:14,080
Chairman, please cancel the search for my mom.

16
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:18,170
No, it's enough.

17
00:01:18,170 --> 00:01:20,400
Thank you.

18
00:01:23,810 --> 00:01:26,120
Kim Ji Young?

19
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:29,380
The US?

20
00:01:29,380 --> 00:01:31,930
Is it Anna Noona?

21
00:01:34,540 --> 00:01:37,430
What am I thinking?

22
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:40,830
Kim Ji Young is a common name.

23
00:01:43,650 --> 00:01:50,750
I guess my mom was a terrible person that I couldn't even meet.

24
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:53,080
But Chairman.

25
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:59,350
Even if everyone says my mom is a bad person,

26
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:02,070
I still want to find her.

27
00:02:02,070 --> 00:02:09,310
I want to see her just once, even from the back.

28
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:17,010
Hello?

29
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:21,270
Please locate Ms. Park Dan Dan's mother, Kim Ji Young, as soon as possible.

30
00:02:21,270 --> 00:02:23,630
Yes, please.

31
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:36,110
Dan Dan agreed to wrap up everything in that house by the end of the week.

32
00:02:36,110 --> 00:02:40,320
Please hurry and finish the documentation to go to the US before she changes her mind.

33
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:42,070
Do it as quickly as possible.

34
00:02:42,070 --> 00:02:48,030
Okay. I will look into a flight for next week.

35
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:52,850
Does that mean I can meet with Dan Dan now?

36
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:57,550
Yes, go ahead.

37
00:02:57,550 --> 00:03:01,720
But don't forget what I told you.

38
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:03,970
Okay. I won't be found out.

39
00:03:03,970 --> 00:03:05,900
I will be careful and more careful.

40
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:10,690
I will make sure she doesn't ever find out I'm her mother.

41
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:12,940
I promise.

42
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:30,290
Oh my, those two, they are meeting again.

43
00:03:32,190 --> 00:03:36,690
Okay, I need to secure evidence.

44
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:44,840
There is something not right about these two.

45
00:03:48,110 --> 00:03:50,200
- Hyung, Hyung.
- Hey, you.

46
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:53,480
Where have you been instead of sweeping here?

47
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:55,410
Look, look at this.

48
00:03:55,410 --> 00:04:01,930
I didn't think Mr. Park was that kind of person, but he met up with that woman again.

49
00:04:01,930 --> 00:04:05,730
Oh my. It really is Mr. Park.

50
00:04:05,730 --> 00:04:08,920
Look at the vibe between Mr. Park and this woman.

51
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:10,700
Doesn't it look like an affair?

52
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:13,250
Mr. Ma.

53
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:17,600
What do you mean? Are you talking about my Soo Chul?

54
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:19,820
This is CEO Anna with my Soo Chul.

55
00:04:19,820 --> 00:04:24,900
So, are you saying you know the woman?

56
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:27,400
Of course. I know her very well.

57
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:30,410
But did you say these two were having an affair?

58
00:04:30,410 --> 00:04:33,910
Pardon? Aigoo, no, we didn't.

59
00:04:33,910 --> 00:04:36,400
He was just talking nonsense.

60
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:38,210
It's not nonsense.

61
00:04:38,210 --> 00:04:42,320
They looked strange to my eyes.

62
00:04:42,350 --> 00:04:45,160
Where was this taken?

63
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:48,730
It's the coffee shop next to the vet over there.

64
00:04:51,340 --> 00:04:53,730
You reckless bastard.

65
00:04:53,730 --> 00:04:57,590
I can't ignore this. I should call Mr. Park and let him know about this.

66
00:04:57,590 --> 00:05:01,330
You can't do this, at least for social justice.

67
00:05:01,330 --> 00:05:05,610
What if a family gets destroyed because of us?

68
00:05:05,610 --> 00:05:09,960
Why is that because of us? It's because of Mr. Park, who had an affair.

69
00:05:20,610 --> 00:05:24,240
He really was with her.

70
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:27,730
Honey.

71
00:05:27,730 --> 00:05:33,450
Why are you looking at her so longingly? Have you been seeing her secretly?

72
00:05:33,450 --> 00:05:35,470
Have you been having an affair with Anna Kim?

73
00:05:35,470 --> 00:05:37,130
What are you saying?

74
00:05:37,130 --> 00:05:40,960
Then why are you meeting with her? When you've decided not to go to the US?

75
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:44,080
I had to see her because of Dan Dan.

76
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:47,660
Dan Dan? What about Dan Dan?

77
00:05:47,660 --> 00:05:51,250
Why are you acting like this on the street? Let's talk at home.

78
00:05:56,770 --> 00:06:03,190
What? Is Dan Dan going to the US with CEO Anna next week?

79
00:06:03,190 --> 00:06:04,760
Yes.

80
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:09,460
That's why I met up with CEO Anna, because of Dan Dan.

81
00:06:09,460 --> 00:06:12,310
If that was the case, you should have told me.

82
00:06:12,310 --> 00:06:16,140
My daughter is going to the US next week, and why did I not know that until now as her mother?

83
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:18,730
Do you even think of me as your wife?

84
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:21,040
Things happened very quickly.

85
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:23,370
I was going to tell you when everything was decided.

86
00:06:23,370 --> 00:06:28,110
But why does everything have to be in such a rush?

87
00:06:28,110 --> 00:06:30,160
It's not like she's going to Jeju Island.

88
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:34,810
If Dan Dan stays in Korea, she won't be able to end it with Chairman Lee.

89
00:06:34,810 --> 00:06:39,880
So I met with CEO Anna to make the request since she's going back to the US next week.

90
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:43,810
Father, did Dan Dan say she would go to the US?

91
00:06:43,810 --> 00:06:45,650
Yes.

92
00:06:45,650 --> 00:06:52,550
Wasn't she saying she would never break up with Chairman Lee? How did she agree to go?

93
00:06:52,550 --> 00:06:59,680
I told her that if she goes to the US for three years to study and work

94
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:04,560
and still can't forget Chairman Lee, I will reconsider their relationship.

95
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,800
So she agreed.

96
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:09,140
Even so, I'm grateful to the CEO.

97
00:07:09,140 --> 00:07:13,420
She's willing to take Dan Dan with her.

98
00:07:13,420 --> 00:07:15,350
Yes.

99
00:07:15,350 --> 00:07:19,540
But Noona, how could you say such absurd things about my brother-in-law?

100
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:21,860
What? An affair?

101
00:07:21,860 --> 00:07:24,320
You are such a troublemaker. A troublemaker.

102
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:28,080
Is Soo Chul someone who'd do such a thing?

103
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:32,370
There would be no misunderstanding if he told me first.

104
00:07:32,370 --> 00:07:35,980
The younger boss at the Jokbal restaurant said something strange.

105
00:07:35,980 --> 00:07:40,360
That younger boss is bad.

106
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:42,510
He goes around gossiping.

107
00:07:42,510 --> 00:07:46,830
The older boss is decent.

108
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:51,820
If you end up splitting with Soo Chul, you can go live with the younger boss at the Jokbal restaurant.

109
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:55,060
Mom!

110
00:07:55,060 --> 00:07:59,430
Dan Dan must be busy getting ready to go to the US.

111
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:01,890
- How come she's not home?
- That's true.

112
00:08:01,890 --> 00:08:07,280
She hasn't told the children about it yet, so after that, she would wrap up her work and come home.

113
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:10,760
The children seemed to like her a lot.

114
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:14,120
I think Unni will be crying when she's leaving the house.

115
00:08:33,070 --> 00:08:38,970
I really can't tell the children I am leaving.

116
00:08:38,970 --> 00:08:44,600
How about if I tell them when you find the new teacher?

117
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,620
I will tell the children.

118
00:08:46,620 --> 00:08:50,830
I think it would be better if I told them.

119
00:08:50,830 --> 00:08:53,450
Okay, I get it.

120
00:09:15,090 --> 00:09:19,750
Se Chan. Se Jong.

121
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:28,790
Ms. Park and I have agreed to go our separate ways.

122
00:09:30,970 --> 00:09:35,970
So she will stop working here.

123
00:09:35,970 --> 00:09:38,960
You can't hold her back this time.

124
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:44,320
It's because she's going to the US with CEO Anna Kim next week.

125
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:50,730
For her future, let's let her go, okay?

126
00:09:52,730 --> 00:09:57,030
I will tell Jenny about this separately.

127
00:09:57,030 --> 00:10:01,610
Since she doesn't know about us, I will only tell her about Ms. Park leaving the job.

128
00:10:01,610 --> 00:10:05,090
You know what I am saying, right?

129
00:10:05,090 --> 00:10:11,110
You and Ms. Park broke up because Ms. Park's father was against you two, wasn't it?

130
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:15,680
Right? This doesn't make any sense!

131
00:10:19,450 --> 00:10:22,770
Se Chan.

132
00:10:22,770 --> 00:10:25,410
People can't live alone.

133
00:10:25,410 --> 00:10:30,650
You also live with me, Jenny, and Se Jong.

134
00:10:30,650 --> 00:10:35,070
Ms. Park also has a family she loves.

135
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:38,630
A family is the biggest shelter for a person.

136
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:41,680
So if the family opposes until the end,

137
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:46,190
even if you love each other very much, you can't just push ahead.

138
00:10:46,190 --> 00:10:50,600
I know you and Se Jong like Ms. Park very much.

139
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:54,940
I am very sorry for saying these things.

140
00:10:54,940 --> 00:10:57,190
Why are you sorry?

141
00:10:57,190 --> 00:11:00,350
It's not your fault that things turned out this way.

142
00:11:00,350 --> 00:11:03,100
Ms. Park told me this a while ago.

143
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:06,620
When you meet someone, you'll have to say goodbye eventually.

144
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:09,650
That's why it happened.

145
00:11:09,650 --> 00:11:13,870
It's okay since it's not your fault.

146
00:11:25,210 --> 00:11:26,990
Yes.

147
00:11:31,230 --> 00:11:35,420
Se Chan. Se Jong.

148
00:11:35,420 --> 00:11:40,150
Ms. Park. We just heard everything from my dad.

149
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:42,920
That you will be leaving us.

150
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:48,100
Ms. Park, are you really going to the US?

151
00:11:50,390 --> 00:11:53,160
Se Chan. Se Jong.

152
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:55,580
I am sorry.

153
00:11:55,580 --> 00:11:57,650
I am so sorry.

154
00:11:57,650 --> 00:12:01,120
Don't be sorry. We are still young,

155
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:03,580
but we understood everything that my dad said.

156
00:12:03,580 --> 00:12:06,850
So, please do not be sorry.

157
00:12:06,850 --> 00:12:11,290
Ms. Park, please be happy in the US.

158
00:12:11,290 --> 00:12:14,730
Thank you, Se Chan and Se Jong.

159
00:12:20,710 --> 00:12:26,180
Se Chan, Se Jong, I will come back in three years.

160
00:12:26,180 --> 00:12:31,090
So please be healthy until then.

161
00:12:36,540 --> 00:12:38,480
Are you really going to quit working here?

162
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:41,810
Is that why you are packing your bags?

163
00:12:41,810 --> 00:12:44,160
That is, Jenny... I will explain everything.

164
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:46,550
How can you quit overnight like this?

165
00:12:46,550 --> 00:12:49,650
I didn't know you were as irresponsible as this.

166
00:12:49,650 --> 00:12:52,360
I am honestly disappointed.

167
00:13:19,910 --> 00:13:21,900
Jenny.

168
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:24,940
Can we talk, please?

169
00:13:24,940 --> 00:13:29,100
I don't want to say anything to you.

170
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:30,830
Jenny.

171
00:13:30,830 --> 00:13:35,490
I am going to the US with CEO Anna.

172
00:13:35,490 --> 00:13:38,290
That's why I had to quit.

173
00:13:38,290 --> 00:13:42,540
I couldn't tell you sooner because it was a sudden decision.

174
00:13:42,540 --> 00:13:45,670
I am really sorry, Jenny.

175
00:13:47,890 --> 00:13:50,340
You said you would stay until March.

176
00:13:50,340 --> 00:13:53,540
How can you break the promise unilaterally?

177
00:13:53,540 --> 00:13:58,140
I don't want to see you. Please get out of my room.

178
00:13:58,140 --> 00:14:00,750
You don't know anything to be speaking like that.

179
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:03,010
You know how much Ms. Park loves us.

180
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:05,980
Don't you think she had an unavoidable reason to do this?

181
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:09,960
A reason? What kind of a reason?

182
00:14:14,380 --> 00:14:16,730
Never mind, she has her reasons.

183
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:19,720
So, don't upset her feelings anymore!

184
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:23,300
That's why I am asking you to tell me.

185
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:27,200
Hyung, please don't.

186
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,530
Ms. Park. Please tell us.

187
00:14:29,530 --> 00:14:31,570
What are the reasons?

188
00:14:31,570 --> 00:14:33,500
No, Jenny.

189
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:37,080
The date for the US departure moved up.

190
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:39,540
I'm so sorry, Jenny.

191
00:14:39,540 --> 00:14:42,160
I am sorry.

192
00:14:44,890 --> 00:14:46,630
Noona, why are you acting like this?

193
00:14:46,630 --> 00:14:50,410
Even if we can't let her go happily, we shouldn't make her sad.

194
00:14:50,410 --> 00:14:54,320
How do you think she feels leaving us behind?

195
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:09,180
Yes.

196
00:15:11,210 --> 00:15:13,660
Jenny.

197
00:15:15,890 --> 00:15:17,730
Ms. Park.

198
00:15:17,730 --> 00:15:21,700
I am sure you have a reason why you had to do this.

199
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:25,080
I'm sorry for acting terribly.

200
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:28,770
It's not because I hate you.

201
00:15:28,770 --> 00:15:32,010
I don't want to say goodbye to you.

202
00:15:32,010 --> 00:15:35,760
But when you said you were leaving suddenly,

203
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:39,000
I was so sad. That's why.

204
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:43,810
Maybe I'm still more immature than Se Chan and Se Jong.

205
00:15:43,810 --> 00:15:48,670
I am really sorry, Ms. Park.

206
00:15:48,670 --> 00:15:53,490
No, Jenny. I'm the one who's sorry.

207
00:15:53,530 --> 00:15:56,970
Please look after Se Chan and Se Jong.

208
00:15:56,970 --> 00:16:00,940
And you have to take good care of yourself too.

209
00:16:00,940 --> 00:16:04,710
I trust you, Jenny.

210
00:16:06,490 --> 00:16:09,790
- Ms. Park.
- Ms. Park.

211
00:16:40,890 --> 00:16:44,670
Ms. Park...

212
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:50,220
Yes.

213
00:16:53,650 --> 00:16:57,240
Oh my dear, what brings you to my room?

214
00:16:57,240 --> 00:17:01,490
Madam. Thank you for everything until now.

215
00:17:01,490 --> 00:17:05,980
I will be leaving after this week.

216
00:17:05,980 --> 00:17:10,830
Oh my! Are you leaving? Really?

217
00:17:10,830 --> 00:17:14,410
Yes. I will be going to the US next week.

218
00:17:14,410 --> 00:17:16,240
The US?

219
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:18,390
Why all of a sudden?

220
00:17:18,390 --> 00:17:22,220
Is Young Gook sending you there?

221
00:17:22,220 --> 00:17:25,620
No, Madam. I got a job in CEO Anna's company.

222
00:17:25,620 --> 00:17:28,090
I will be leaving with her.

223
00:17:28,090 --> 00:17:31,750
Oh, CEO Anna.

224
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,830
Then...

225
00:17:33,830 --> 00:17:36,460
What happens with Young Gook?

226
00:17:36,460 --> 00:17:40,950
Did you split? Did you break up?

227
00:17:40,950 --> 00:17:43,080
Yes.

228
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:45,490
Oh, really!

229
00:17:45,490 --> 00:17:47,400
You made the right decision!

230
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,080
It's good that you broke up with him.

231
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:52,550
Yes, you and Young Gook are really not a good match.

232
00:17:52,550 --> 00:17:56,160
That's the right thing to do.

233
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:59,370
Maybe because you're young, you're good at understanding my words.

234
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:02,140
With your sensibility, you will do well in the US, too.

235
00:18:02,140 --> 00:18:05,710
I hope you achieve the American Dream there.

236
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:11,560
I hope you meet a guy of your age over there, get married, and have children.

237
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:13,620
I will get going.

238
00:18:13,630 --> 00:18:16,740
Okay.

239
00:18:22,460 --> 00:18:25,500
It feels liberating.

240
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:28,470
I feel alive now.

241
00:18:28,470 --> 00:18:31,370
Oh, my...

242
00:18:35,870 --> 00:18:38,030
Ms. Park, what's this?

243
00:18:38,030 --> 00:18:42,000
Is this a goodbye gift?

244
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:45,970
You've looked after me and stood by my side all this time.

245
00:18:45,970 --> 00:18:49,010
Thank you very much.

246
00:18:49,010 --> 00:18:53,430
Thank you. It was nice to have you since I could rely on you.

247
00:18:53,430 --> 00:18:56,220
It's such a shame for you to go. I'm sad.

248
00:18:58,190 --> 00:19:01,420
But how did you decide to go to the US all of a sudden?

249
00:19:01,420 --> 00:19:02,760
Who are you going with?

250
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:05,210
I got a job at CEO Anna's company.

251
00:19:05,210 --> 00:19:08,200
So I will be leaving with her next week.

252
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:10,810
Really? That's great.

253
00:19:10,810 --> 00:19:13,380
She's a really good person.

254
00:19:13,380 --> 00:19:15,940
Yes, she is.

255
00:19:15,940 --> 00:19:19,670
She's always treated me well, like a daughter.

256
00:19:19,670 --> 00:19:23,530
Maybe she's been extra good to you because she has no family.

257
00:19:23,530 --> 00:19:26,090
According to the lady who worked here before me,

258
00:19:26,090 --> 00:19:30,960
