Yes. She broke up with Young Gook and quit her tutor job.

565
00:40:24,950 --> 00:40:28,660
She's going to America with CEO Anna.

566
00:40:28,660 --> 00:40:31,990
She's going to America with CEO Anna?

567
00:40:31,990 --> 00:40:37,700
Yes! Driver Park adamantly opposed the relationship between Ms. Park and Young Gook.

568
00:40:37,700 --> 00:40:42,890
I thought Ms. Park's family planned it all to seduce our Young Gook.

569
00:40:42,890 --> 00:40:45,160
But seeing how Driver Park is totally opposed,

570
00:40:45,160 --> 00:40:49,350
I guess I might have thought it wrong.

571
00:40:49,350 --> 00:40:51,550
I see.

572
00:40:52,920 --> 00:40:57,220
We've gotten rid of Ms. Park, that bothersome vixen.

573
00:40:57,220 --> 00:41:00,760
At the time like now, if Young Gook looks back at you,

574
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:04,790
it would be great. But that cold bastard!

575
00:41:17,600 --> 00:41:20,900
Hello, Jo Sarah.

576
00:41:20,900 --> 00:41:25,250
Are you trying to restart with the Chairman? Are you?

577
00:41:25,250 --> 00:41:29,590
But what's with this car? Have you opened a flower shop?

578
00:41:51,420 --> 00:41:54,500
Sarah, let's talk.

579
00:41:54,500 --> 00:42:01,310
If you come and bother me like this, I will report you to the police.

580
00:42:01,310 --> 00:42:06,490
I'm really sorry for the last time. I want to apologize.

581
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:15,690
Sarah. I really regret breaking up with you.

582
00:42:15,690 --> 00:42:19,470
Sarah. Where is our son?

583
00:42:19,470 --> 00:42:21,290
You gave birth to my son.

584
00:42:21,290 --> 00:42:27,110
I want to find our son and three of us to start again.

585
00:42:27,110 --> 00:42:33,080
What? Where did you hear such nonsense?

586
00:42:33,080 --> 00:42:35,730
Do you really want to die?

587
00:42:35,730 --> 00:42:38,220
Get out. Get out, you bastard.

588
00:42:38,220 --> 00:42:39,720
- I said, get out!
- Hey!

589
00:42:39,720 --> 00:42:41,840
Get out!

590
00:42:47,780 --> 00:42:51,400
Sarah, let's talk again later.

591
00:42:53,800 --> 00:42:55,470
Oh no, Ajussi!

592
00:42:55,470 --> 00:42:57,940
- That punk is here again.
- I'm so sorry.

593
00:42:57,940 --> 00:43:00,180
What did he threaten you with today?

594
00:43:00,180 --> 00:43:02,580
I told you to call me when he comes.

595
00:43:02,580 --> 00:43:04,710
What should I do?

596
00:43:04,710 --> 00:43:07,240
Did you hear me? Call me.

597
00:43:07,240 --> 00:43:09,450
Answer me, please.

598
00:43:09,450 --> 00:43:13,160
Ajussi, why are you like this to me? Please don't be good to me!

599
00:43:13,160 --> 00:43:17,430
I'm more bothered by you than that bastard.

600
00:43:23,360 --> 00:43:26,520
Hey, Mi Sook!

601
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:29,440
- Hey!
- What? Oh, my!

602
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:32,140
Aren't these scallion pancakes?

603
00:43:32,140 --> 00:43:35,670
I've been craving something like this. How did you know?

604
00:43:35,670 --> 00:43:37,710
I know you like scallion pancakes.

605
00:43:37,710 --> 00:43:39,760
Try some.

606
00:43:39,760 --> 00:43:42,330
Oh, really.

607
00:43:42,330 --> 00:43:43,950
How is it?

608
00:43:43,950 --> 00:43:47,770
By the way, you look great.

609
00:43:47,770 --> 00:43:52,470
You said you couldn't sleep. Did you fix your insomnia?

610
00:43:52,470 --> 00:43:54,990
Yes.

611
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:57,290
That's good.

612
00:43:57,290 --> 00:43:59,430
Sleep is the best medicine at our age.

613
00:43:59,430 --> 00:44:02,850
If we don't get enough sleep, we can get sick with every ailment.

614
00:44:02,850 --> 00:44:04,110
That's right, yes.

615
00:44:04,110 --> 00:44:05,700
Eat it with this sauce.

616
00:44:05,700 --> 00:44:07,730
Next is heartwarming news.

617
00:44:07,730 --> 00:44:14,880
Last January, an anonymous donor left 500 million won in front of Soojung Orphanage, which became a hot topic.

618
00:44:14,880 --> 00:44:17,950
To relay their gratitude,

619
00:44:17,950 --> 00:44:23,060
the orphanage is looking for an anonymous donor who gave the wonderful gift.

620
00:44:23,060 --> 00:44:29,010
The anonymous donor is presumed to be a woman in her late fifties.
[The Orphanage is in search of an anonymous donor who made a 500 million won donation to thank them]

621
00:44:29,010 --> 00:44:30,680
Oh, my world. 500 million won?

622
00:44:30,680 --> 00:44:32,300
She disappeared in a hurry.

623
00:44:32,300 --> 00:44:37,150
In the bag, she left a note, "Please spend this on something good for the children."

624
00:44:37,150 --> 00:44:42,090
It's me who made that donation.

625
00:44:42,090 --> 00:44:46,150
Does that mean they are looking for me right now?

626
00:44:46,150 --> 00:44:50,200
The orphanage said they wanted to find the donor to thank them.

627
00:44:50,230 --> 00:44:54,730
What's wrong, Gi Ja?

628
00:44:54,730 --> 00:45:00,070
It's nothing. The drink went down the wrong pipe.

629
00:45:00,070 --> 00:45:05,690
I don't know who's that donor, but that person is great.

630
00:45:05,690 --> 00:45:12,370
How could they donate not 5 million won or 50 million won, but 500 million won?

631
00:45:12,370 --> 00:45:17,730
That person will go to heaven for sure.

632
00:45:17,730 --> 00:45:23,010
My goodness, Gi Ja. You are covered in a cold sweat.

633
00:45:23,010 --> 00:45:25,260
This is not okay.

634
00:45:25,260 --> 00:45:29,640
You should go to the hospital and get a comprehensive physical exam.

635
00:45:29,640 --> 00:45:34,230
Do you have some internal illness?

636
00:45:34,230 --> 00:45:37,640
What?

637
00:45:37,650 --> 00:45:41,290
Right, I should do it.

638
00:45:41,290 --> 00:45:42,910
Right...

639
00:45:42,910 --> 00:45:46,540
What do you think, Ms. Park? Aren't these colors pretty?

640
00:45:46,540 --> 00:45:47,880
Yes, they are so pretty.

641
00:45:47,880 --> 00:45:49,440
Which one do you like more?

642
00:45:49,440 --> 00:45:53,080
I don't think I can choose.

643
00:45:53,080 --> 00:45:56,620
- Why don't you try these on?
- Okay.

644
00:46:10,960 --> 00:46:12,240
It's beautiful.

645
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:16,470
Ms. Park. I think these will suit you very nicely.

646
00:46:16,470 --> 00:46:19,670
CEO Anna, you've already bought me too much.

647
00:46:19,670 --> 00:46:21,400
I think we could stop now.

648
00:46:21,400 --> 00:46:26,430
You will be my employee now. Can't I do this much?

649
00:46:26,430 --> 00:46:27,630
But still.

650
00:46:27,630 --> 00:46:29,420
Think of it as a uniform I'm buying for you.

651
00:46:29,420 --> 00:46:31,860
Hurry, let's go inside.

652
00:46:48,370 --> 00:46:50,810
Yes, it's me.

653
00:46:50,810 --> 00:46:53,040
Now?

654
00:46:55,560 --> 00:46:58,060
What's the problem?

655
00:47:00,480 --> 00:47:02,570
Okay.

656
00:47:11,060 --> 00:47:13,050
I'll be out for a few minutes.

657
00:47:13,050 --> 00:47:14,980
Where are you going?

658
00:47:14,980 --> 00:47:17,380
Someone came to see me nearby.

659
00:47:17,380 --> 00:47:19,380
Okay.

660
00:47:21,940 --> 00:47:24,670
Mom, I'll be out for a few minutes.

661
00:47:24,670 --> 00:47:27,650
If you all go out, what can I do by myself?

662
00:47:27,650 --> 00:47:30,760
- I'm back.
- Dae Beom's here.

663
00:47:32,570 --> 00:47:34,110
What's going on with my mom?

664
00:47:34,110 --> 00:47:36,420
I don't know.

665
00:47:46,650 --> 00:47:49,870
Excuse me.

666
00:47:49,870 --> 00:47:53,580
Where did he go?

667
00:48:01,180 --> 00:48:04,210
What's going on?

668
00:48:04,210 --> 00:48:07,710
I went shopping with Dan Dan just now.

669
00:48:07,710 --> 00:48:15,320
We talked while we were shopping. She seemed like she's gotten herself together.

670
00:48:15,320 --> 00:48:20,330
It seems like she's firmly decided on going to the US.

671
00:48:20,330 --> 00:48:23,210
She should be.

672
00:48:23,240 --> 00:48:26,160
I'm relieved. All the documentation is complete.

673
00:48:26,160 --> 00:48:30,810
And I've bought the plane tickets. We are ready to go.

674
00:48:30,810 --> 00:48:34,670
That's good.

675
00:48:34,670 --> 00:48:39,240
You could have told me that on the phone.

676
00:48:39,240 --> 00:48:46,160
I have something to give you so that I asked you to see me.

677
00:48:48,550 --> 00:48:51,420
Please take this.

678
00:48:51,420 --> 00:48:52,790
What is it?

679
00:48:52,790 --> 00:48:56,240
I feel sorry to you for everything until now.

680
00:48:56,240 --> 00:48:59,850
And thankful for many things.

681
00:48:59,850 --> 00:49:05,170
Think of it as child support for raising Dan Dan or alimony if you'd like.

682
00:49:05,170 --> 00:49:08,200
I'm so grateful that you are sending Dan Dan away with me.

683
00:49:08,200 --> 00:49:10,730
- That's why.
- What?

684
00:49:10,730 --> 00:49:12,830
Do you think I'm sending Dan Dan to give her to you?

685
00:49:12,830 --> 00:49:15,440
Don't delude yourself. I told you this before.

686
00:49:15,440 --> 00:49:18,110
Do not reveal you are her mother.

687
00:49:18,110 --> 00:49:19,490
Child Support?

688
00:49:19,490 --> 00:49:23,480
You are simply CEO Anna to our Dan Dan. Got it?

689
00:49:23,480 --> 00:49:26,680
What do you mean she's Dan Dan's mother?

690
00:49:26,700 --> 00:49:29,480
What is going on here?

691
00:49:37,650 --> 00:49:39,530
Is this woman Dan Dan's mother?

692
00:49:39,530 --> 00:49:43,320
This woman, Anna Kim, is?

693
00:49:43,320 --> 00:49:45,360
That makes no sense.

694
00:49:45,360 --> 00:49:48,100
Have you two been seeing each other behind my back?

695
00:49:48,100 --> 00:49:50,890
Deceiving me all this time?

696
00:49:50,890 --> 00:49:52,620
How can you do this to me?

697
00:49:52,620 --> 00:49:54,910
No, Honey, that's not it. Just a minute.

698
00:49:54,910 --> 00:49:56,350
Let's go talk outside.

699
00:49:56,350 --> 00:49:58,040
Is this woman Dan Dan's mother?

700
00:49:58,040 --> 00:50:01,870
Is that why you were going to go to America with this woman?

701
00:50:01,870 --> 00:50:04,220
How can you do this to me? How?

702
00:50:04,220 --> 00:50:05,530
Let's talk outside.

703
00:50:05,530 --> 00:50:08,330
Let go of me. Let go!

704
00:50:08,330 --> 00:50:09,830
- Let go!
- Honey!

705
00:50:09,830 --> 00:50:12,100
Let go of me.

706
00:50:12,100 --> 00:50:14,480
Let go of me!

707
00:50:20,510 --> 00:50:21,600
Just come out.

708
00:50:21,600 --> 00:50:25,150
Let go. Let go of me!

709
00:50:25,150 --> 00:50:27,690
Out of all people, how can you do this to me?

710
00:50:27,690 --> 00:50:31,100
Honey, calm down and listen to me.

711
00:50:31,100 --> 00:50:32,980
It's not what you think.

712
00:50:32,980 --> 00:50:36,920
Didn't you say she was Dan Dan's mother?

713
00:50:36,920 --> 00:50:39,220
Yes, she is. That's right.

714
00:50:39,220 --> 00:50:43,200
So, were you going to go to the US with her and Dan Dan

715
00:50:43,200 --> 00:50:45,790
and set up a new household together?

716
00:50:45,790 --> 00:50:47,290
How can you do that to me?

717
00:50:47,290 --> 00:50:49,060
Do you think I'm crazy?

718
00:50:49,060 --> 00:50:51,900
You know how much I hate and despise that woman.

719
00:50:51,900 --> 00:50:54,220
But you were going to go to the US with her!

720
00:50:54,220 --> 00:50:57,090
That's when I didn't know who she was!

721
00:50:57,090 --> 00:51:01,350
I also didn't know she was Dan Dan's mother at first!

722
00:51:01,350 --> 00:51:03,110
What?

723
00:51:03,110 --> 00:51:06,010
What do you mean?

724
00:51:08,020 --> 00:51:10,120
Think back carefully.

725
00:51:10,120 --> 00:51:14,020
That woman doesn't have Dan Dan's mother's face.

726
00:51:14,020 --> 00:51:16,710
Dan Dan's mother's face?

727
00:51:18,460 --> 00:51:24,500
That's right. That's not the face I saw twenty-seven years ago.

728
00:51:24,500 --> 00:51:26,040
What happened?

729
00:51:26,040 --> 00:51:27,860
She had a huge accident ten years ago.

730
00:51:27,860 --> 00:51:30,750
And undergone more than ten plastic surgeries on her face.

731
00:51:30,750 --> 00:51:32,690
So I didn't recognize her at first as well.

732
00:51:32,690 --> 00:51:36,840
When I found out she was Dan Dan's mother, I refused to go to the US.

733
00:51:36,840 --> 00:51:40,840
That's why I didn't go even though you insisted that I should go.

734
00:51:40,840 --> 00:51:43,050
Is that really true?

735
00:51:43,050 --> 00:51:45,550
Then why are you sending Dan Dan to her now?

736
00:51:45,550 --> 00:51:47,870
Why do you think I'm sending her?

737
00:51:47,870 --> 00:51:50,730
It's because I have no other option.

738
00:51:50,730 --> 00:51:53,310
Dan Dan hasn't blossomed yet.

739
00:51:53,310 --> 00:51:56,860
Do you want her to live raising Chairman Lee's children? That's why I'm sending her.

740
00:51:56,860 --> 00:52:00,650
Since she's Dan Dan's mother, at least.

741
00:52:00,650 --> 00:52:04,970
So you are saying there was nothing else between you and her.

742
00:52:04,970 --> 00:52:07,600
Of course not!

743
00:52:10,650 --> 00:52:16,900
Honey, so please trust me and pretend you don't know about this.

744
00:52:16,900 --> 00:52:22,100
Dan Dan won't go to the US with her if Dan Dan finds out she's the mother who abandoned her.

745
00:52:22,100 --> 00:52:26,550
Honey, once Dan Dan leaves for the US next week, it'll all be over.

746
00:52:26,550 --> 00:52:28,240
I will have no reasons to see her again.

747
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:32,400
So please, Honey. Will you?

748
00:52:44,010 --> 00:52:47,480
Nothing won't go wrong, will it be?

749
00:52:50,900 --> 00:52:52,900
Thankfully, I could move on.
[Soo Chul Oppa]

750
00:52:52,900 --> 00:52:57,420
My wife decided to pretend that she didn't know.

751
00:52:57,420 --> 00:53:01,610
As we promised, please take good care of our Dan Dan.

752
00:53:04,130 --> 00:53:06,680
That's a relief.

753
00:53:06,680 --> 00:53:10,930
Thank you. Thank you.

754
00:53:24,650 --> 00:53:27,060
Se Jong.

755
00:53:27,060 --> 00:53:29,520
Se Jong, where are you?

756
00:53:29,520 --> 00:53:32,320
Dad, what is it?

757
00:53:32,320 --> 00:53:34,340
Jenny and Se Chan, have you seen Se Jong?

758
00:53:34,340 --> 00:53:36,840
He was in his room earlier.

759
00:53:36,840 --> 00:53:38,510
He's not in his room.

760
00:53:38,510 --> 00:53:41,370
Let's look for him.

761
00:53:46,160 --> 00:53:49,270
Dad, wait a minute.

762
00:53:53,560 --> 00:53:57,900
Dad and Noona! Se Jong is here.

763
00:54:02,330 --> 00:54:05,440
Se Jong, why are you here?

764
00:54:05,440 --> 00:54:10,650
Dad, when is Ms. Park coming?

765
00:54:16,830 --> 00:54:21,360
I guess you miss Ms. Park.

766
00:54:22,740 --> 00:54:26,280
Se Jong, Ms. Park would go to America

767
00:54:26,280 --> 00:54:28,260
and said she would come back later.

768
00:54:28,260 --> 00:54:33,190
So is Ms. Park really not coming now?

769
00:54:34,970 --> 00:54:36,950
Should we go to your room now?

770
00:54:36,950 --> 00:54:39,400
It's past your bedtime.

771
00:54:39,400 --> 00:54:41,510
Dad...

772
00:54:41,510 --> 00:54:46,040
I can't sleep since Ms. Park is not here.

773
00:54:46,040 --> 00:54:49,770
Then, should we go to sleep together?

774
00:54:51,180 --> 00:54:55,030
I want to go to bed with you and Se Jong, too.

775
00:54:55,030 --> 00:54:57,670
Shall we? What about you, Jenny?

776
00:54:57,670 --> 00:55:00,410
I'm fine.

777
00:55:00,410 --> 00:55:03,540
Okay. Se Chan and Se Jong,

778
00:55:03,540 --> 00:55:06,960
let's sleep together in dad's room tonight.

779
00:55:14,640 --> 00:55:18,740
Your brother already fell asleep, but are you still having trouble sleeping?

780
00:55:18,740 --> 00:55:24,090
Yes. Dad, I can't sleep.

781
00:55:25,960 --> 00:55:29,620
Then, let me count numbers from one for you.

782
00:55:29,620 --> 00:55:31,840
You'll fall asleep soon.

783
00:55:31,840 --> 00:55:33,820
Okay.

784
00:55:36,020 --> 00:55:38,450
One.

785
00:55:38,450 --> 00:55:40,800
Two.

786
00:55:40,810 --> 00:55:43,340
Three.

787
00:55:43,340 --> 00:55:46,000
Four.

788
00:55:46,000 --> 00:55:48,910
Five.

789
00:55:48,910 --> 00:55:51,440
Six...

790
00:55:51,440 --> 00:55:54,060
Seven...

791
00:56:01,670 --> 00:56:05,700
Se Jong, are you okay? What should I do?

792
00:56:13,810 --> 00:56:15,380
Yes, it's me.

793
00:56:15,380 --> 00:56:18,550
Oppa. I think you have to come home right now.

794
00:56:18,550 --> 00:56:20,470
Something's wrong with Se Jong.

795
00:56:20,470 --> 00:56:23,020
I think he's very sick.

796
00:56:23,020 --> 00:56:26,400
What? Is Se Jong sick?

797
00:56:34,020 --> 00:56:37,570
Se Jong got sensitive since he was very sleep-deprived,

798
00:56:37,570 --> 00:56:40,450
so I prescribed a tranquilizer.

799
00:56:40,450 --> 00:56:45,810
Dr. Kim, Se Jong never had this kind of issue before.

800
00:56:45,810 --> 00:56:49,040
I think it's a symptom of separation anxiety.

801
00:56:49,040 --> 00:56:51,130
Separation anxiety?

802
00:56:51,130 --> 00:56:52,980
Yes.

803
00:56:52,980 --> 00:56:58,100
If he can't sleep or eat and continues to vomit,

804
00:56:58,100 --> 00:57:00,880
he needs counseling and hospitalization.

805
00:57:00,880 --> 00:57:06,720
But I think this happened from the shock of his tutor resigning suddenly.

806
00:57:06,720 --> 00:57:13,550
So I think for her to come back and to calm Se Jong is the best solution.

807
00:57:13,550 --> 00:57:16,400
Ah, okay...

808
00:57:24,530 --> 00:57:27,260
The more I think about it, it's ridiculous.

809
00:57:27,260 --> 00:57:29,630
Anna Kim, that wench is absurd.

810
00:57:29,630 --> 00:57:31,960
She even changed her face with plastic surgery.

811
00:57:31,960 --> 00:57:34,980
Didn't she approach my Soo Chul on purpose?

812
00:57:34,980 --> 00:57:37,510
And she came to me, talking about money

813
00:57:37,510 --> 00:57:40,410
and trying to take my husband away from me?

814
00:57:40,410 --> 00:57:43,210
I won't leave that wench alone.

815
00:57:44,720 --> 00:57:48,680
Open the door! I said, open the door!

816
00:57:59,920 --> 00:58:02,980
- Why are you doing this? Please stop!
- Why am I doing this?

817
00:58:02,980 --> 00:58:04,660
You thief wench!

818
00:58:04,660 --> 00:58:07,410
You even changed your face and came back.

819
00:58:07,410 --> 00:58:09,580
How dare you try to take my Soo Chul away?

820
00:58:09,580 --> 00:58:12,420
This evil wench. This scary wench!

821
00:58:12,420 --> 00:58:13,970
You thief wench!

822
00:58:13,970 --> 00:58:19,400
How dare you change your face and show up when you abandoned your infant daughter!

823
00:58:19,400 --> 00:58:21,850
You thief wench!

824
00:58:23,590 --> 00:58:27,520
If you contact my husband one more time, I won't stand still.

825
00:58:27,520 --> 00:58:30,880
I'm putting up with you because of my Dan Dan!

826
00:58:30,880 --> 00:58:32,560
Do you understand?

827
00:58:32,560 --> 00:58:34,720
How can you show up by changing your face?

828
00:58:34,720 --> 00:58:38,650
You scammer, thief wench!

829
00:59:10,710 --> 00:59:13,330
Soo Chul.

830
00:59:13,330 --> 00:59:15,600
It's me.

831
00:59:17,340 --> 00:59:21,210
How long do I have to suffer my hair getting pulled?

832
00:59:21,210 --> 00:59:23,870
What do you mean by that?

833
00:59:23,870 --> 00:59:26,010
Did my wife come by again?

834
00:59:26,010 --> 00:59:31,860
How long do I have to suffer like this!

835
00:59:31,860 --> 00:59:36,200
You're the one who told me to take Dan Dan to America with me.

836
00:59:36,200 --> 00:59:39,600
Can't you talk reason into her?

837
00:59:39,600 --> 00:59:45,270
What if Dan Dan sees your wife coming at me like this?

838
00:59:53,410 --> 00:59:56,670
When did you come home?

839
00:59:56,670 --> 00:59:59,290
Seriously, what are you doing?

840
00:59:59,290 --> 01:00:02,490
Why did you go there again?

841
01:00:04,660 --> 01:00:06,890
Did that wench already call you?

842
01:00:06,890 --> 01:00:09,510
Are you two secretly communicating with each other?

843
01:00:09,510 --> 01:00:11,340
It's ridiculous.

844
01:00:11,340 --> 01:00:14,490
Are you siding with her in front of me now?

845
01:00:14,490 --> 01:00:17,420
Honey, please.

846
01:00:17,420 --> 01:00:20,290
Can you please tolerate until Dan Dan goes?

847
01:00:20,290 --> 01:00:23,090
If you want to vent, please vent on me.

848
01:00:23,090 --> 01:00:30,330
Are you that sad because Dan Dan's birth mother got hit by me?

849
01:00:30,330 --> 01:00:34,100
How could you only think of her instead of my broken heart?

850
01:00:34,100 --> 01:00:36,630
By saying a hundred thousand, two hundred thousand dollars!

851
01:00:36,630 --> 01:00:41,800
She tricked me! Thinking of that made me infuriated, so I grabbed her by her hair.

852
01:00:41,800 --> 01:00:45,240
But does that breaks your heart that much?

853
01:00:45,240 --> 01:00:49,760
She changed her face and even tried to seduce you.

854
01:00:49,760 --> 01:00:52,280
But how can I not get angry!

855
01:00:52,280 --> 01:00:56,790
Honey, calm down. It's not that I don't know your feelings.

856
01:00:56,790 --> 01:01:01,290
But I'm worried that Dan Dan might find out if you keep acting like this.

857
01:01:01,290 --> 01:01:03,390
Honey, it's not late to reconsider.

858
01:01:03,390 --> 01:01:06,600
I don't think you should send Dan Dan with that woman.

859
01:01:06,600 --> 01:01:10,400
She will use Dan Dan to seduce you.

860
01:01:10,400 --> 01:01:13,830
She'll use Dan Dan as an excuse to call you to America.

861
01:01:13,830 --> 01:01:15,850
How am I supposed to endure that?

862
01:01:15,850 --> 01:01:19,870
It's like giving a fish to a cat!

863
01:01:19,870 --> 01:01:24,920
Does it make sense to send Dan Dan to the mother that abandoned her?

864
01:01:26,220 --> 01:01:31,490
What are you saying now?

865
01:01:31,490 --> 01:01:37,850
The one who will take Dan Dan to America is Dan Dan's mother?

866
01:01:37,850 --> 01:01:41,580
Mother-in-law... The thing is...

867
01:01:49,260 --> 01:01:51,630
Father, I don't think it's right.

868
01:01:51,630 --> 01:01:55,100
How would Dan Dan feel if she knew about it later?

869
01:01:55,100 --> 01:01:58,980
She would feel betrayed. This is not okay.

870
01:02:00,440 --> 01:02:02,480
I don't think it's right, too.

871
01:02:02,480 --> 01:02:05,270
I also think it's not right.

872
01:02:05,270 --> 01:02:11,320
I mean, it's her mother who's taking Dan Dan, so she'll take good care of her in America.

873
01:02:11,320 --> 01:02:16,430
It might be okay if this secret can be kept forever.

874
01:02:16,430 --> 01:02:22,270
But no secret can be kept forever.

875
01:02:22,270 --> 01:02:28,700
Honey, you should tell Dan Dan everything now.

876
01:02:28,700 --> 01:02:31,220
It's not that she likes a thief.

877
01:02:31,220 --> 01:02:34,930
There are only two things that he has three kids, and he is older than her.

878
01:02:34,930 --> 01:02:37,140
Do you have to do this far?

879
01:02:37,140 --> 01:02:39,680
Honey, please stop.

880
01:02:39,680 --> 01:02:43,250
If we all keep it secret, there won't be a problem.

881
01:02:43,250 --> 01:02:46,290
How will Dan Dan find out about it if she goes to America?

882
01:02:46,290 --> 01:02:48,910
Since that woman also promised to keep the secret forever,

883
01:02:48,910 --> 01:02:54,370
I want you to endure for Dan Dan until she goes.

884
01:02:54,370 --> 01:02:58,790
If Dan Dan goes to America, she can forget about everything and start anew.

885
01:03:01,240 --> 01:03:07,720
Sure. Dan Dan's your daughter. We don't have any rights.

886
01:03:07,720 --> 01:03:12,270
But if she knows about it later, it'll be a big problem.

887
01:03:12,270 --> 01:03:15,460
That's why we are worrying about it.

888
01:03:15,460 --> 01:03:17,450
But I get it.

889
01:03:18,720 --> 01:03:21,370
Don't worry, Mother-in-law.

890
01:03:21,370 --> 01:03:24,320
It'll be all over when she leaves in two days.

891
01:03:24,320 --> 01:03:28,330
That woman promised me that she wouldn't tell the fact that she was Dan Dan's mother until her death.

892
01:03:28,330 --> 01:03:30,080
So please don't worry.

893
01:03:30,080 --> 01:03:37,230
Also, if you go to America to see her or you contact her in secret,

894
01:03:37,230 --> 01:03:42,370
I'll call Dan Dan and tell her that woman is her mother.

895
01:03:42,370 --> 01:03:44,630
You better make that clear.

896
01:03:44,630 --> 01:03:46,880
It won't happen, so don't worry.

897
01:03:46,880 --> 01:03:49,320
I'm home.

898
01:03:51,780 --> 01:03:55,750
What is it? Why is everyone being quiet since I come in?

899
01:03:55,750 --> 01:04:00,300
It's suspicious. Were you talking bad about me?

900
01:04:00,300 --> 01:04:04,080
Wow, you're a genius. How did you know we were talking bad about you?

901
01:04:04,080 --> 01:04:06,220
What? Is it true?

902
01:04:06,220 --> 01:04:08,380
I'm kidding.

903
01:04:09,720 --> 01:04:13,290
We talked about how empty it would be since you're going to America.

904
01:04:13,290 --> 01:04:16,000
Why don't you change into comfy clothes? Let's have a beer.

905
01:04:16,000 --> 01:04:19,900
Beer sounds great! Okay, I'll come out in a second.

906
01:04:24,580 --> 01:04:29,370
Please keep it secret so that Dan Dan can go to America.

907
01:04:29,370 --> 01:04:31,150
I got it.

908
01:04:31,150 --> 01:04:34,910
Everybody, watch your words.

909
01:05:11,820 --> 01:05:16,590
Look! There are many dishes that Se Jong likes.

910
01:05:16,590 --> 01:05:21,530
Se Jong, would you like to try a shrimp?

911
01:05:23,520 --> 01:05:25,260
Se Jong,

912
01:05:25,260 --> 01:05:29,370
you like sausages, right? Why don't you have this?

913
01:05:37,820 --> 01:05:41,220
What should we do?

914
01:05:41,220 --> 01:05:46,440
Se Jong, you don't have to eat it. If you don't want to eat, it's okay.

915
01:05:46,440 --> 01:05:51,470
Let's have some rest with me in your room, Se Jong.

916
01:05:54,510 --> 01:05:56,670
Let's go.

917
01:06:01,040 --> 01:06:05,320
I think his separation anxiety is not fake!

918
01:06:05,320 --> 01:06:08,420
What should we do?

919
01:06:19,010 --> 01:06:24,410
Se Jong, if you don't want to eat, you don't have to eat.

920
01:06:24,410 --> 01:06:26,160
Okay?

921
01:06:26,160 --> 01:06:27,850
Yes.

922
01:06:29,640 --> 01:06:34,840
But you told me that you want to become a cool soccer player when you grow up.

923
01:06:34,840 --> 01:06:39,480
If you don't eat anything like now, you won't grow tall nor have strength,

924
01:06:39,480 --> 01:06:43,510
so I wonder if you can kick the soccer ball nicely.

925
01:06:43,510 --> 01:06:46,950
Since you have to become an incredible soccer player,

926
01:06:46,950 --> 01:06:52,220
should I make some plain rice porridge for you?

927
01:06:54,610 --> 01:06:58,510
I don't want to eat anything right now.

928
01:06:58,510 --> 01:07:00,990
Can you make that for me tomorrow?

929
01:07:00,990 --> 01:07:05,120
Okay. Please close your eyes and have a good sleep.

930
01:07:05,120 --> 01:07:08,380
When you have a good night's sleep, you'll feel better.

931
01:07:08,380 --> 01:07:14,280
But Dad, I want to sleep, but I can't.

932
01:07:14,280 --> 01:07:18,290
Then, should I count numbers for you?

933
01:07:18,290 --> 01:07:20,700
Dad.

934
01:07:20,700 --> 01:07:28,840
You counted numbers for me more than 500 last night,

935
01:07:28,840 --> 01:07:31,260
but I couldn't sleep.

936
01:07:31,260 --> 01:07:37,890
Dad, I feel like I can sleep if Ms. Park comes.

937
01:07:52,730 --> 01:07:55,010
That one looks great on you!

938
01:07:55,010 --> 01:07:57,340
Wear these glasses, too!

939
01:07:58,550 --> 01:08:01,380
One, two, three!

940
01:08:03,930 --> 01:08:07,250
Ms. Park, be happy in America as well.

941
01:08:07,250 --> 01:08:09,800
Ms. Park!

942
01:08:25,900 --> 01:08:28,390
Wow, look at that!

943
01:08:28,390 --> 01:08:30,360
Bye, kite!

944
01:08:30,360 --> 01:08:32,690
Goodbye!

945
01:08:32,690 --> 01:08:34,250
Bye-bye.

946
01:08:34,250 --> 01:08:36,390
Bye-bye!

947
01:08:54,890 --> 01:08:56,580
Yes, Chairman.

948
01:08:56,580 --> 01:08:59,800
Ms. Park.

949
01:08:59,800 --> 01:09:04,350
I'm sorry to call you this late.

950
01:09:04,350 --> 01:09:08,000
But can you please come here just once?

951
01:09:08,000 --> 01:09:11,620
I'm sorry? Right now?

952
01:09:13,650 --> 01:09:21,220
♫ Why do you run away, love
?
Like a shy child ♫

953
01:09:21,220 --> 01:09:27,990
♫ In case I lose it, I hold it tight ♫

954
01:09:27,990 --> 01:09:35,050
♫ But love always runs away, chased by longing ♫

955
01:09:35,050 --> 01:09:41,940
♫ It would be nice to take a break ♫

956
01:09:41,940 --> 01:09:49,840
♫ I have to abandon the longing and the grieves ♫

957
01:09:49,840 --> 01:09:55,800
♫ What am I looking for on this road wandering ♫

958
01:09:55,800 --> 01:09:58,120
♫ Why am I here for what ♫

959
01:09:58,120 --> 01:10:01,390
[Young Lady and Gentleman]

960
01:10:01,390 --> 01:10:04,830
What are you doing right now? You promised me to let Dan Dan go.

961
01:10:04,830 --> 01:10:06,470
- How shameless!
- I'm sorry.

962
01:10:06,470 --> 01:10:09,940
I'm going to the US in two days! So stop acting like this to the Chairman.

963
01:10:09,940 --> 01:10:11,690
- Let's play this!
- I don't know how to play it.

964
01:10:11,690 --> 01:10:12,690
Enjoy your meal.

965
01:10:12,690 --> 01:10:14,050
Hello, Uncle.

966
01:10:14,050 --> 01:10:17,790
I broke up with Dae Beom, but strangely it doesn't feel like we did.

967
01:10:17,790 --> 01:10:19,190
Don't try to push it like that.

968
01:10:19,190 --> 01:10:22,310
I forgot to bring the USB that has today's fashion show's materials.

969
01:10:22,310 --> 01:10:24,150
Could you go to my place?

970
01:10:24,150 --> 01:10:26,410
This looks just like my baby photo.

971
01:10:26,410 --> 01:10:27,620
Isn't it Chief Jo?

972
01:10:27,620 --> 01:10:29,610
She's coming twice a week to do the flowers.

973
01:10:29,610 --> 01:10:30,930
Does my brother know about this?

974
01:10:30,930 --> 01:10:32,280
It would be better if you didn't come here.

975
01:10:32,280 --> 01:10:34,680
Are you saying CEO Anna Kim is Park Dan Dan's birth mother?

976
01:10:34,680 --> 01:10:36,460
- I would like to see you for a moment.
- Alright.

977
01:10:36,460 --> 01:10:39,750
That's right. She is your birth mom.

978
01:10:39,750 --> 01:10:43,430
Is CEO Anna my mom?
